==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Galliambic
<hw>Gal`li*am"bic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>galliambus</ets> a song used by the priests of Cybele;
<ets>Gallus</ets> (a name applied to these priests) +
<ets>iambus</ets>]</ety> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>Consisting of two
iambic dimeters catalectic, the last of which lacks the final syllable;
-- said of a kind of verse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gallian</ent>⟦br⟧
